   - So, $f(2) = | \lfloor 2 \rfloor | = |2| = 2$.

2. **$f(-\pi)$:**
   - $\pi$ is irrational.
   - So, $f(-\pi) = (\lceil -\pi \rceil)^2$.
   - $-\pi \approx -3.14159$, so $\lceil -\pi \rceil = -3$.
